// tasks - git repo and track those files
first command - git init
git init → current folder ko Git repository bana deta hai (new repo start).
Repo start karta hai.

Second command :->ls → folder ke normal files/folders dikhata hai.
                  ls -al → saari files (hidden bhi) + detailed info (permissions, owner, size, date) dikhata hai.
                  ls = simple list
                  ls -al = all + details

3.> git Status :-> 
git status → batata hai repo ki current state: kaunsi files modified, staged ya untracked hain.
Repo ka haal batata hai.

4.> git add text.txt 
git add → modified/untracked files ko staging area me daalta hai, taaki next commit me jaa sake.
Commit ke liye files ready karta hai.

5.> git commit space :->
git commit → staged changes ko permanent snapshot bana deta hai with a message.
Common code:
git commit -m "message"
Changes save karta hai (history me).

6.> git log → repo ke saare commits ka history dikhata hai (author, date, message).
Commit history show karta hai.
